description.narrative: BCO supported municipalities on COVID-19 prevention through WASH/IPC training, reaching 15,908 health professionals in PHCFs. PPE and supplies were also distributed to support health systems. UNICEF advocated for COVID-19 vaccines and routine immunization and is promoting an innovative intersectoral strategy (BAV) to improve vaccine coverage that will be implemented in UNICEF Seal municipalities. More than 36,000 adolescents received psychosocial support through an innovative platform during the pandemic. BCO gathered evidence for strong recommendations for the sustainability of the Youth Aware strategy as a public policy to promote HIV testing and treatment for young people. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2022
